liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: At least 13 Palestinians have been reported dead from the same family when an Israeli airstrike hit their house in Khan Younis. The fresh bombardment hit the building where the Al-Batta and Al-Majayda family were living, survivors told Reuters. People stood in dismay, while others panicked as they rushed to get stretchers to pull survivors. Children covered in dust were carried into ambulances. Reuters
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Airstrike reportedly leaves 13 members of a single family dead

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: By Adelaide Miller Dr Bob Bowker, the former Australian ambassador to Egypt, Jordan and Syria, says it is of "profound regret" that US President Joe Biden did not formally recommend a ceasefire during his visit to Israel this week. Speaking with ABC PM's David Lipson, Dr Bowker says the "Arab world is looking for two things at the moment" – a ceasefire and an "American approach" that will find a political solution. "The critical thing now is for the US to insist that Israel has a vision for the day after in Gaza … to justify the bloodshed that will follow", Dr Bowker says. "For now, both sides are staring into the void".
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 'Profound regret' Biden did not formally push ceasefire, former ambassador says

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Russia has sent 27 ton of humanitarian aid for civilians in the Gaza Strip to be transported from Egypt, according to their emergency situations ministry. "A special plane has taken off from the airport at Ramenskoye near Moscow for El-Arish in Egypt," deputy minister Ilya Denisov said. "The Russian humanitarian aid will be handed over to the Egyptian Red Crescent to be sent to the Gaza Strip,." He said the aid comprised "wheat, sugar, rice (and) pasta".
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Russia says it sent 27 tons of humanitarian aid to Gaza

children.content: Russia has sent 27 ton of humanitarian aid for civilians in the Gaza Strip to be transported from Egypt, according to their emergency situations ministry.
"A special plane has taken off from the airport at Ramenskoye near Moscow for El-Arish in Egypt," deputy minister Ilya Denisov said.
"The Russian humanitarian aid will be handed over to the Egyptian Red Crescent to be sent to the Gaza Strip,."
He said the aid comprised "wheat, sugar, rice (and) pasta".
